  "response": "Tata Motors produces a variety of cars, including:\n\n**Hatchbacks:**\n\n*   **Tata Tiago:** A popular and affordable hatchback.\n*   **Tata Altroz:** A premium hatchback known for its safety and design.\n\n**Sedans:**\n\n*   **Tata Tigor:** A compact sedan based on the Tiago.\n\n**SUVs:**\n\n*   **Tata Punch:** A micro SUV known for its high ground clearance and rugged design.\n*   **Tata Nexon:** A subcompact SUV, one of Tata's best-selling models.\n*   **Tata Harrier:** A mid-size SUV with a bold design.\n*   **Tata Safari:** A 6/7-seater SUV, the flagship model.\n\n**Electric Vehicles (EVs):**\n\n*   **Tata Tiago EV:** The electric version of the Tiago hatchback.\n*   **Tata Tigor EV:** The electric version of the Tigor sedan.\n*   **Tata Nexon EV:** The electric version of the Nexon SUV, a popular EV option.\n*   **Tata Punch EV:** The electric version of the Punch micro SUV.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Availability:** The models available can vary depending on your region.\n*   **Updates:** Tata Motors regularly updates its models with new features and technologies.\n*   **Future Models:** Tata Motors is continuously developing new models, including electric vehicles, so the lineup may change over time.\n*   **Discontinued Models:** Tata Motors has discontinued the production and sales of several models, including the Indica, Indigo, Manza, Bolt, Zest, and Nano.\n\nFor the most up-to-date information, you should visit the official Tata Motors website for your region.\n",
